The paper discusses joint source-channel coding in the context of network communication, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and network communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of the proposed architecture in relay communication, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the hybrid coding scheme, which could be evaluated using machine learning techniques (cs.MM) or statistical learning (cs.LG).
